Houston Business Journal







 






Bizspace Spotlight
        





 Sponsor Listing 



                    Property Spotlight: PV|303 - Arizona’s Rising Hub For Business Expansion                




See All Bizspace Properties



 
 











 Enlarge





                Houston-based Forum Energy Technologies Inc., global oil field products company, has… more 

                Cathy Proctor | Denver Business Journal            








 



Houston-based Forum Energy Technologies Inc. (NYSE: FET) has promoted Prady Iyyanki to president.
He takes over the role from Christopher Gaut, who remains chairman and CEO. Iyyanki also will remain COO, a role he has held since January 2014.













 Enlarge






                            Houston-based Forum Energy Technologies Inc., global oil field products company, has… more 
Cathy Proctor | Denver Business Journal










 


Iyyanki, who was a private investor from March 2013 to December 2013, has held many roles with different General Electric Co. (NYSE: GE) businesses.
He served as a vice president at GE Oil and Gas from April 2011 to March 2013. He also served as president and CEO of the GE Oil and Gas Turbo Machinery business from April 2011 to December 2012 and as president and CEO of the GE Power and Water Gas Engines business from June 2006 to April 2011.




He has a Bachelor of Science in Engineering from Jawaharlal Nehru Technology University in India and a Master of Science in Engineering from South Dakota State University.
Last year, Forum Energy Technologies ranked as the Houston area’s 72nd-largest public company, based on its 2014 revenue of $1.74 billion. It reported 2015 revenue of $1.07 billion, down 38 percent.
The global oil field products company serves the subsea, drilling, completion, production and infrastructure sectors. It went public in 2012.

Olivia Pulsinelli is the senior web editor for the Houston Business Journal's award-winning website. Follow her on Twitter for more.











 






